	(5036,656,'_timeline_items_7_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5037,656,'timeline_items_7_timeline_description','In October of 2013, the core leadership from Cordillera formed a new venture under the name of FourPoint Energy. This fourth enterprise is the first company funded by direct equity investments and term debt rather than from a private equity fund. The initial geographic focus will be in the core areas of the Western Anadarko and Permian Basins.'),
	(5038,656,'_timeline_items_7_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5039,656,'timeline_items_7_timeline_image','131'),
	(5040,656,'_timeline_items_7_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5041,656,'timeline_items_8_timeline_year','2014'),
	(5042,656,'_timeline_items_8_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5043,656,'timeline_items_8_timeline_description','On January 30th, 2014 FourPoint Energy announced the closing of certain producing and underdeveloped properties in the Western Anadarko Basin from EnerVest, Ltd. Under terms of the agreement, FourPoint purchased for $269 million, an ownership stake in both the Laredo and SM Energy acquisitions closed by EnerVest in the fourth quarter of 2013. The acquisition included interest in 1500 producing wells with net production to FourPoint of 30 Mmcfgd.  FourPoint and EnerVest also entered into a Joint Development Agreement and Area of Mutual Interest to own, operate and develop oil and gas properties in the Western Anadarko Basin. The partnership combines the extensive technical, operational and transactional expertise of both companies while launching a well-capitalized venture to capture future opportunities through acquisitions and the drill bit.  Simultaneous with the negotiation of the asset purchase and Joint Development Agreement, FourPoint closed on the funding of its initial equity and debt capitalization totaling over $200 million in direct private equity and a term debt facility with capacity to fund $800 million. In November 2014 the current term notes facility expanded their debt capitalization to $1.25 billion and an additional $200 million in equity was raised.  Key acquisitions throughout the year positioned the joint venture to boast an acreage position of more than [325,000] net acres in the established AMI with net production exceeding [315] Mmcfed.'),
	(5044,656,'_timeline_items_8_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5045,656,'timeline_items_8_timeline_image','132'),
	(5046,656,'_timeline_items_8_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5047,656,'timeline_items_9_timeline_year','2015'),
	(5048,656,'_timeline_items_9_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5049,656,'timeline_items_9_timeline_description','In August 2015, FourPoint exclusive of the Joint Venture closed on one of its most instrumental acquisitions from Chesapeake Exploration L.L.C. and CHK Cleveland Tonkawa, L.L.C for a purchase price of $840 million. The acquisition added just under 130 Mmcfed in production from 1,509 wells, 684 Bcfe in proved reserves and nearly 250,000 net acres. To fund these acquisitions, FourPoint grew its balance sheet to over 2.5 billion in capitalization, approximately half of which is equity from 81 private shareholders. In order to operationally manage and develop this asset FourPoint opened up its first field office located in Woodward, Oklahoma.'),
