	(5815,702,'page_description','After building three successful energy companies in 12 years, the only thing left to do was to start a fourth. FourPoint Energy is an exploration and production company founded by the leadership team of Cordillera Energy Partners. With over 30 years of industry leadership, FourPoint has a history to support its future growth to seek its greatest untapped resource: Opportunity.'),
	(5816,702,'_page_description','field_56f0d08ab57b3'),
	(5817,702,'timeline_items_0_timeline_year','2000'),
	(5818,702,'_timeline_items_0_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5819,702,'timeline_items_0_timeline_description','Cordillera Energy Partners was founded in February 2000 and incorporated as a Limited Liability Company formed in the state of Texas. The Company formed by George Solich, President and CEO, and his management team, employed the “acquire/exploit” strategy—buying producing assets and underdeveloped assets in three core areas. They enhanced production, cash flow, and reserves through a combination of drilling and lowering the cost structure, while adding additional “bolt-on” acquisitions.'),
	(5820,702,'_timeline_items_0_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5821,702,'timeline_items_0_timeline_image','129'),
	(5822,702,'_timeline_items_0_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5823,702,'timeline_items_1_timeline_year','2003'),
	(5824,702,'_timeline_items_1_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5825,702,'timeline_items_1_timeline_description','The core areas for Cordillera Energy Partners I (CEP I) were the Anadarko Basin, the Delaware Basin and the San Juan Basin. Through a combination of acquisitions and drilling, CEP I grew its production to 30 MMCFED, annual cash flow to $35 million, and proved reserves to 250 BCFE by mid-2003. In October 2003, CEP I sold its assets to Patina Oil & Gas for cash and warrants to purchase Patina stock valued at $247 million.'),
	(5826,702,'_timeline_items_1_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5827,702,'timeline_items_1_timeline_image','130'),
	(5828,702,'_timeline_items_1_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5829,702,'timeline_items_2_timeline_year','2004'),
	(5830,702,'_timeline_items_2_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5831,702,'timeline_items_2_timeline_description','Upon completion of the CEP I sale, the core management team formed CEP II, again with EnCap Investments, seven along-side institutional investors and management. In March of 2004, the company was capitalized with a $200 million private equity investment and a $300 million credit facility from six banks led by JP Morgan Chase. CEP II added to its management team ranks and set out to chart the same “acquire/exploit” strategy that had been so successful in CEP I.'),
	(5832,702,'_timeline_items_2_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5833,702,'timeline_items_2_timeline_image','131'),
	(5834,702,'_timeline_items_2_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5835,702,'timeline_items_3_timeline_year','2007'),
	(5836,702,'_timeline_items_3_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5837,702,'timeline_items_3_timeline_description','Prior to the sale of CEP II, the management team and CEP’s equity investors elected to form CEP III, LLC, while still managing and operating CEP II so as not to lose momentum, opportunities, or talent. In March of 2007, CEP III was formed with a $500 million equity investment from EnCap Investments, along-side institutional investors and management. CEP III also entered into a $600 million, six bank credit facility again led by JP Morgan Chase.'),
	(5838,702,'_timeline_items_3_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5839,702,'timeline_items_3_timeline_image','132'),
	(5840,702,'_timeline_items_3_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5841,702,'timeline_items_4_timeline_year','2008'),
	(5842,702,'_timeline_items_4_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5843,702,'timeline_items_4_timeline_description','Through a combination of focused acquisitions and vertical and horizontal drilling, CEP II grew quickly in both size and value. By mid-2008 CEP II was producing close to 50 MMCFED from 600 wells (97% operated with annual cash flow exceeding $200 million and proved reserves of 725 BCFE.) These high-quality natural gas assets were concentrated in the Texas Panhandle (Douglas, Cleveland, Granite Wash, Atoka, and Morrow), West Central Anadarko Basin, and the East Texas Basin (Cotton Valley Sand, Cotton Valley Lime, Houston, Pettet, and Travis Peak).  \r\n\r\n\r\nIn September of 2008 CEP II sold all the assets of the company in three separate transactions for total consideration in cash and stock valued at $1.023 billion. The Texas Panhandle and East Texas assets were sold to Forest Oil, the Oklahoma assets to Merit Energy, and the Deep Woodford assets to Devon Energy.'),
	(5844,702,'_timeline_items_4_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5845,702,'timeline_items_4_timeline_image','134'),
	(5846,702,'_timeline_items_4_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5847,702,'timeline_items_5_timeline_year','2010'),
	(5848,702,'_timeline_items_5_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5849,702,'timeline_items_5_timeline_description','CEP III held assets and operations in the Texas Panhandle, Western Oklahoma, and the East Texas Basin. During this period, the Cordillera management team executed on both small and large producing property and acreage acquisitions totaling over $700 million and has drilled over 235 wells (vertical and horizontal) investing over $300 million.'),
	(5850,702,'_timeline_items_5_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5851,702,'timeline_items_5_timeline_image','131'),
	(5852,702,'_timeline_items_5_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5853,702,'timeline_items_6_timeline_year','2012'),
	(5854,702,'_timeline_items_6_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5855,702,'timeline_items_6_timeline_description','In January of 2012, CEP III agreed to merge with Apache Corporation of Houston, Texas. Under the terms of the agreement, Apache acquired CEP III for $2.85 billion comprised of $600 million in common shares and $2.25 billion in cash. CEP III’s producing property and acreage acquisitions combined with its active drilling program in the Texas Panhandle and Western Oklahoma enabled the company to grow production and cash flow at a compound annual growth rate of 70%. CEP III held one of the leading acreage positions in the Western Anadarko Basin with over 14,000 engineered locations. The merger closed on April 1, 2012, incorporating closing adjustments as well as additional acreage and drilling, Apache paid $3.1 billion. At closing, CEP III delivered close to 330,000 net acres with production over 24,000 BOEPD from over 600 producing wells.'),
	(5856,702,'_timeline_items_6_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5857,702,'timeline_items_6_timeline_image','130'),
	(5858,702,'_timeline_items_6_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5859,702,'timeline_items_7_timeline_year','2013'),
	(5860,702,'_timeline_items_7_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5861,702,'timeline_items_7_timeline_description','In October of 2013, the core leadership from Cordillera formed a new venture under the name of FourPoint Energy. This fourth enterprise is the first company funded by direct equity investments and term debt rather than from a private equity fund. The initial geographic focus is the Western Anadarko and Permian Basins.'),
	(5862,702,'_timeline_items_7_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5863,702,'timeline_items_7_timeline_image','131'),
	(5864,702,'_timeline_items_7_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5865,702,'timeline_items_8_timeline_year','2014'),
	(5866,702,'_timeline_items_8_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5867,702,'timeline_items_8_timeline_description','On January 30th, 2014 FourPoint Energy announced the closing of certain producing and underdeveloped properties in the Western Anadarko Basin from EnerVest, Ltd. Under terms of the agreement, FourPoint purchased for $269 million, an ownership stake in both the Laredo and SM Energy acquisitions closed by EnerVest in the fourth quarter of 2013. The acquisition included interest in 1500 producing wells with net production to FourPoint of 30 Mmcfgd.  FourPoint and EnerVest also entered into a Joint Development Agreement and Area of Mutual Interest to own, operate and develop oil and gas properties in the Western Anadarko Basin. The partnership combines the extensive technical, operational and transactional expertise of both companies while launching a well-capitalized venture to capture future opportunities through acquisitions and the drill bit.  Simultaneous with the negotiation of the asset purchase and Joint Development Agreement, FourPoint closed on the funding of its initial equity and debt capitalization totaling over $200 million in direct private equity and a term debt facility with capacity to fund $800 million. In November 2014 the current term notes facility expanded their debt capitalization to $1.25 billion and an additional $200 million in equity was raised.  Key acquisitions throughout the year positioned the joint venture to boast an acreage position of more than [325,000] net acres in the established AMI with net production exceeding [315] Mmcfed.'),
	(5868,702,'_timeline_items_8_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5869,702,'timeline_items_8_timeline_image','132'),
	(5870,702,'_timeline_items_8_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5871,702,'timeline_items_9_timeline_year','2015'),
	(5872,702,'_timeline_items_9_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5873,702,'timeline_items_9_timeline_description','​In August 2015, FourPoint closed on another sizable and well-positioned acquisition in the Western Anadarko Basin. FourPoint, exclusive of participation with its Joint Venture partner, EnerVest, purchased operation assets in Oklahoma from Chesapeake Exploration L.L.C. and CHK Cleveland Tonkawa, L.L.C for a purchase price of $840 million. The acquisition added just under 130 Mmcfed in production from 1,509 wells, 684 Bcfe in proved reserves and nearly 250,000 net acres. To fund these acquisitions, FourPoint grew its balance sheet to over 2.5 billion in capitalization, approximately half of which is equity from 81 private shareholders. In order to operationally manage and develop this asset FourPoint opened up its first field office located in Woodward, Oklahoma.'),
	(5874,702,'_timeline_items_9_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
