	(215,2,'2016-03-30 22:25:12','2016-03-30 22:25:12','While success in business and being the best is always at the forefront of the FourPoint organization, giving back provides the balance the team needs to remain focused. FourPoint Energy values Compassionate Stewardship and strives to positively impact the lives of employees, partners, landowners, and shareholders by caring for and about people, communities, assets and performance.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1202\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/community-1.jpg\" alt=\"community-1\" width=\"1165\" height=\"1005\" />\r\n\r\nThe team at FourPoint takes pride in being able to give back and make a difference in people\'s lives, not only within the communities where employees live and work, but also on a national and global level. <del data-redactor-tag=\"del\"></del>FourPoint demonstrates support and community involvement in a variety of ways, from sponsored golf tournaments, luncheons, charitable donations, adopt-a-family programs, and numerous sponsored events within their operating communities.\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy believes in taking an active role for supporting local initiatives. The company is an active member of the:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The Quarterly Forum</li>\r\n 	<li>Kynd Hub</li>\r\n 	<li>Canadian Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Wheeler Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Cheyenne - Roger Mills Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Elk City Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em>“We appreciate being part of the business community in the Texas Panhandle and Western Oklahoma. Our sponsorship and volunteer support of community groups and events is a small way to show our support for the communities where we live and work”</em> – George Solich, President &amp; CEO','Community Engagement','','publish','closed','closed','','community-engagement','','','2016-06-15 21:18:55','2016-06-15 21:18:55','',90,'http://fourpointenergy.com/?page_id=215',0,'page','',0),
