	(251,2,'2016-03-31 18:45:49','2016-03-31 18:45:49','FourPoint Energy, LLC\r\n\r\n100 St. Paul Street, Suite 400\r\nDenver, CO 80206\r\n\r\n(303) 290-0990 Main\r\n(303) 290-9997 Fax\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAll Owner Inquiries\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Phone:</strong> (303) 785-1581\r\n\r\nYou will be prompted to leave a message when contacting our owner inquiry line. Please leave your:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Name</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone Number</li>\r\n	<li>Owner Number</li>\r\n	<li>A brief description of your inquiry</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYour owner number is the five digit number located in the bottom left corner of your check stub, or the top right hand corner of your joint owner statement.\r\n\r\nEvery effort will be made to make an initial response to your inquiry within 24 hours. Please do not leave more than one message as this will delay our response time.\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Email:</strong>\r\n\r\nAccounting Inquiries: <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</u></a>\r\n\r\n<u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">Division Owner Inquiries: <a href=\"mailto:divisionorders@fourpointenergy.com\">divisionorders@fourpointenergy.com</a></u>','Contact Information','','inherit','closed','closed','','200-revision-v1','','','2016-03-31 18:45:49','2016-03-31 18:45:49','',200,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/03/31/200-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(252,2,'2016-03-31 18:53:34','2016-03-31 18:53:34','There are many misunderstandings and false ideals about what oil and gas companies really do to produce energy for America. In fact a large population of people don’t really even think about how they themselves even use energy outside of filling up the gas tank. For just a minute, step back and think about getting in your car, riding a bus, train, or plane, coming home and flipping on a light switch, turning on that fireplace, or the simple use of hot water. Those are all relatively common uses of energy but have you ever thought about how that same energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels is being used to make plastics, synthetic materials, TV’s, shoes, medicines, and even toothpaste? There are numerous other simple and far more complex examples we could toss out there, but the bottom line is each and every one of them use energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels.\r\n\r\nThere are many great educational websites, articles, and publications available for you to learn more about the industry, but more specifically for you to be able to make an accurate and educated opinion about the importance of this enormously valuable natural resources we have right here in America.\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Alex Epstein “The Moral Case for Fossil Fuels” Video Link</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Get the Facts:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Example 1</li>\r\n	<li>Example 2</li>\r\n	<li>Example 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Information &amp; Educational Websites Links:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>CNG Now <a href=\"http://www.cngnow.com/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.cngnow.com</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>Coloradoans for Responsible Energy Development <a href=\"http://www.cred.org/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.cred.org</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>Energy from Shale <a href=\"http://www.energyfromshale.org/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.energyfromshale.org</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>America’s Natural Gas Alliance <a href=\"http://www.anga.us/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.anga.us</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>Uncovering North American Energy <a href=\"http://www.uncoverenergy.com/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.uncoverenergy.com</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>Energy Tomorrow <a href=\"http://www.energytomorrow.org/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.energytomorrow.org</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>Energy In Depth <a href=\"http://www.energyindepth.com/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.energyindepth.com</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>U.S. Energy Information Administration <a href=\"http://www.eia.gov/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.eia.gov</u></a></li>\r\n	<li>Baker Hughes <a href=\"http://www.bakerhughes.com/\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">www.bakerhughes.com</u></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Articles &amp; Publications:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The United States of Gas By: Robert Hefner</li>\r\n	<li>The Basics: Well to Wheel By: COGA</li>\r\n	<li>The Arc of History By: J.P. Morgan</li>\r\n	<li>Worldwide Energy Fact Sheet By: (Source TBD – Brent working on)</li>\r\n</ul>','Inside Energy','','inherit','closed','closed','','212-revision-v1','','','2016-03-31 18:53:34','2016-03-31 18:53:34','',212,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/03/31/212-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(253,2,'2016-03-31 18:57:03','2016-03-31 18:57:03','While success in business and being the best is always at the forefront of the FourPoint organization, giving back provides the balance the team needs to remain focused. FourPoint Energy values Compassionate Stewardship by striving to positively impact the lives of employees, partners, landowners, and shareholders by caring for and about people, communities, assets and performance.\r\n\r\nThe team at FourPoint takes pride in being able to give back and make a difference in peoples’ lives, not only within the communities where employees live and work, but also on a national and global level. FourPoint values being a strong corporate citizen and encourages employees to enhance their quality of life by helping others both corporately and individually. FourPoint demonstrates support and community involvement in a variety of ways, from sponsored golf tournaments, luncheons, charitable donations, adopt-a-family programs, and numerous sponsored events within their operating communities.\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy believes in taking an active role for supporting local initiatives. The company is an active member of the:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Quarterly Forum</li>\r\n	<li>Kynd Hub</li>\r\n	<li>Canadian Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n	<li>Wheeler Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n	<li>Cheyenne - Roger Mills Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n	<li>Canadian Rodeo</li>\r\n	<li>Arnett Rodeo</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n“We appreciate being part of the business community in the Texas Panhandle and Western Oklahoma. Our sponsorship and volunteer support of community groups and events is a small way to show our support for the communities where we live and work” – George Solich, President &amp; CEO','Community Engagement','','inherit','closed','closed','','215-revision-v1','','','2016-03-31 18:57:03','2016-03-31 18:57:03','',215,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/03/31/215-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(254,2,'2016-03-31 18:58:09','2016-03-31 18:58:09','At FourPoint, our industry is energy but our business is opportunity. Check out how your opportunities can grow alongside ours. To view all of our current openings and to apply, please click here. [iCims Third Party Portal]\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy is a leading independent privately owned exploration and production company based in Denver, Colorado with a field office in Woodward, Oklahoma. We are committed to creating value that makes a difference by practicing and living out our values (hyperlink) that define us as an organization.','Join Our Team','','inherit','closed','closed','','218-revision-v1','','','2016-03-31 18:58:09','2016-03-31 18:58:09','',218,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/03/31/218-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(255,2,'2016-03-31 18:59:49','2016-03-31 18:59:49','Building on the experience of three very successful Cordillera companies over the last 15 years, you can expect our team at FourPoint to be deliberate and driven. We approach every day by making good decision with a sense of urgency. Although our name has changed, FourPoint Energy possesses the same passion for creating value for our shareholders, the same commitment to working “Better, Smarter, Faster”, and the same dedication to community stewardship.\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy promotes an opportunistic, performance-driven, and goal-oriented culture. Starting at the top with our executive management team moving across all functional areas we have a strong team-oriented approach to developing strategy, making decisions, and executing our plan. Since the company’s inception we have been blessed with dedicated employees, top-quality equity and debt partners, and high-quality assets to pursue investment of acquisition and drilling dollars. Our company culture focuses on creating value for shareholders with a hard-working, loyal, and technically advanced team of professionals.\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy is proud to partner with landowners, mineral owners, drilling companies, service companies, suppliers, gatherers, transporters, consultants, and all our constituents in the responsible development of natural resources. We value our alliance and partnership with these constituents and approach each relationship with respect and integrity. The goal is to be the buyer of choice, lessee of choice, driller of choice, investment of choice, employer of choice, and eventually, seller of choice. We consider ourselves “Energy Farmers” and respect the land and its opportunity for multiple uses.\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Our Values:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Shared Vision – Creating an organization of people who share a long-term perspective driven to create value and enhance their quality of life.</li>\r\n	<li>Committed Teamwork – Fostering a respectful and inclusive environment to collaborate across functions, embracing the talents of individuals and trusting one another to make the best decisions.</li>\r\n	<li>Empowering People – Entrusting our people with responsibility and authority while making them accountable to our mission, values, and goals.</li>\r\n	<li>Driven to Excellence – Committing to deliberate and continuous improvement and striving to be the best with passion, integrity and humility.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneurial – capturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking and strategic relationships.</li>\r\n	<li>Compassionate Stewardship – positively impacting the lives of our employees, partners, landowners and shareholders by caring for and about people, communities, assets and performance.</li>\r\n</ul>','Company Culture','','inherit','closed','closed','','221-revision-v1','','','2016-03-31 18:59:49','2016-03-31 18:59:49','',221,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/03/31/221-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(256,2,'2016-03-31 19:02:57','2016-03-31 19:02:57','FourPoint Energy is proud to offer its employees a top-of-the-line benefits program, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medical Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Dental Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Life and Long-Term Disability Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Paid Sick Leave</li>\r\n	<li>Paid Holidays</li>\r\n	<li>401k with Employer Match</li>\r\n	<li>Annual Bonus Potential</li>\r\n	<li>4 1/2 Day Workweek</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEmployees can take advantage of vacation time tied to industry experience, and what we fondly call “ebb time” after we’ve successfully completed a significant acquisition or transaction. Employees have used this time, which doesn’t count toward vacation time, to take long awaited family vacations, go on mission trips, work on home projects, and do community service.\r\n\r\nAnd the best part? Everyone shares in the company’s financial success. Employees receive a considerable portion of their compensation through performance-based incentives, including equity ownership.','Company Culture','','inherit','closed','closed','','221-revision-v1','','','2016-03-31 19:02:57','2016-03-31 19:02:57','',221,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/03/31/221-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
