	(294,1,'2016-06-15 21:42:08','2016-06-15 21:42:08','<h3>Why lease or sell to FourPoint Energy?</h3>\n<h4><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1028\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/infograph_businesopps.jpg\" alt=\"infograph_businesopps\" width=\"1475\" height=\"1075\" /></h4>\n<strong>1. Aggressive Offers</strong>\n\nWe pay at or above market based terms and are experienced to move quickly on simple or complex trades.\n\n<strong>2. Defined Areas of Focus</strong>\n\nOur leasing is focused on areas where FourPoint actively drills and operates.\n\n<strong>3. Active Developer</strong>\n\nWe are not an asset warehouse. Our business strategy employs an acquisition development model that accelerates the pace of value creation.\n\n<strong>4. Financial Strength</strong>\n\nAs a privately funded company, we have a strong balance sheet with over $3 billion of committed capital and backing from some of the largest funds in private equity.\n\n<strong>5. Highly Experienced Team</strong>\n\nOur team of engineers, geologists, landman and other professionals have a strong experience base. We are committed to capturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking, and strategic relationships. This translates to being able to execute on leasing, drilling and acquisitions in the most efficient and effective manner.\n\n<strong>6. Experienced Vertical and Horizontal Driller</strong>\n\nWe have a dedicated team of drilling and completion engineers as well as development geologists that have drilled and completed over 500 operated wells in the last 16 years with nearly 300 of those in the modern horizontal environment.\n\n<strong>7. Active Producing Property Buyer</strong>\n\nWith over 30 years of demonstrated acquisition experience to evaluate and pay for producing and undeveloped reserves, FourPoint has closed dozens of acquisition transactions ranging in size from less than $1 million to $1 billion.\n\n<strong>8. Responsible Operator</strong>\n\nWe are a prudent, responsible, low cost operator. We have a disciplined approach to efficiency and cost reduction. Our technical team is highly experienced in drilling and completions in both horizontal and vertical wells. We are committed to the safe and environmentally responsible development of our energy resources and invest time and resources to improve the communities in which we live and work.\n\n<strong>9. Relationship Driven</strong>\n\nOur acquisition strategy incorporates a win-win philosophy to deal making. We strive to build long-term relationships and partnerships that lead to additional transactions down the road. We walk the talk by doing what we say we’re going to do.\n\n<strong>10. Farmouts and Joint-Ventures</strong>\n\nWe encourage owners to provide us the opportunity to accelerate the development of their acreage via farmout or joint-venture agreements.\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact for Leasing</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Scott Haselwood</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;\">Senior Land Advisor, Manager of Leasing\n<strong>D</strong> (303) 785-1547\n<strong>F</strong> (303) 290-9997\n<strong>C</strong> (720) 877-1564\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact for Asset Sales</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Brad Marvin</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Vice President, Business Development\n<strong>D</strong> (303) 785-1554\n<strong>F</strong> (303) 290-9997\n<strong>C</strong> (303) 974-0275\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\n\n</div>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"></h3>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Main areas of focus for leasing and asset acquisitions:</b></span></h3>\nActive Plays:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Western Anadarko Basin\nThe Western Anadarko Basin is located in western Oklahoma and the eastern panhandle of Texas.  This prolific hydrocarbon province contains dense vertical well control and is characterized over twenty gas and oil productive horizons across an area of that covers over 5 million acres.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Delaware Basin</strong>\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The Delaware Basin, spanning portions of both West Texas and SE New Mexico, is the western of the two sub-basins found within the Greater Permian Basin.  Prolific production of both oil and gas from thick accumulations of hydrocarbon saturated Permian age sediments provide multiple stacked target opportunities. The productive fairway of intervals such as the Delaware Group, Avalon, Bone Spring, and Wolfcamp cover an area of more than 5 million acres.</span></li>\n 	<li>Midland Basin\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The Midland Basin of West Texas is the eastern of the two sub-basins found within the Greater Permian Basin. This dominantly oil producing region is characterized by thick accumulations of Permian age sediments, with a productive fairway spanning close to 6 million acres. Thousands of feet of hydrocarbon saturated column including intervals such as the Spraberry, Wolfcamp, and Cline provide multiple stacked target opportunities across this broad region.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2> Operating Counties:</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Texas:</strong> Hansford, Hemphill, Hutchinson, Lipscomb, Ochiltree, Roberts and Wheeler</li>\n 	<li><strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Oklahoma:</strong> Beckham, Blaine, Caddo, Canadian, Cleveland, Comanche, Custer, Dewey, Ellis, Garvin, Grady, McClain, Roger Mills, Washita and Woodward</li>\n</ul>','Business Opportunities','','inherit','closed','closed','','71-autosave-v1','','','2016-06-15 21:42:08','2016-06-15 21:42:08','',71,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/04/04/71-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(295,1,'2016-04-04 22:10:53','2016-04-04 22:10:53','<h3>Why lease or sell to FourPoint Energy?</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><h4>Aggressive Offers:</h4> We pay at or above market based terms and are experienced to move quickly on simple or complex trades.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Defined Areas of Focus:</h4> Our leasing is focused on areas where FourPoint actively drills and operates.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Active Developer:</h4> We are not an asset warehouse. Our business strategy employs an acquisition development model that accelerates the pace of value creation.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Financial Strength:</h4> As a privately funded company, we have a strong balance sheet with over $2.5 billion of committed capital and backing from some of the largest funds in private equity.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Highly Experienced Team:</h4> Our team of engineers, geologists, landman and other professionals have a strong experience base. We are committed to capturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking, and strategic relationships. This translates to being able to execute on leasing, drilling and acquisitions in the most efficient and effective manner.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Experienced Vertical and Horizontal Driller:</h4> We have a dedicated team of drilling and completion engineers as well as development geologists that have drilled and completed over 320 operated wells in the last 16 years with nearly 200 of those in the modern horizontal environment.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Active Producing Property Buyer:</h4> With over 30 years of demonstrated acquisition experience to evaluate and pay for producing and undeveloped reserves, FourPoint has closed over ___ acquisition transactions ranging in size from less than $1 million to $1 Billion.</li>\r\n	<li><h4>Responsible Operator:</h4> We are a prudent, responsible, low cost operator. We have a disciplined approach to efficiency and cost reduction. Our technical team is highly experienced in drilling and completions in both horizontal a