	(862,2,'2016-05-24 16:53:12','2016-05-24 16:53:12','<h3>Why lease or sell to FourPoint Energy?</h3>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></h4>\r\n<strong>Aggressive Offers</strong>\r\n\r\nWe pay at or above market based terms and are experienced to move quickly on simple or complex trades.\r\n\r\n<strong>Defined Areas of Focus</strong>\r\n\r\nOur leasing is focused on areas where FourPoint actively drills and operates.\r\n\r\n<strong>Active Developer</strong>\r\n\r\nWe are not an asset warehouse. Our business strategy employs an acquisition development model that accelerates the pace of value creation.\r\n\r\n<strong>Financial Strength</strong>\r\n\r\nAs a privately funded company, we have a strong balance sheet with over $2.5 billion of committed capital and backing from some of the largest funds in private equity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Highly Experienced Team</strong>\r\n\r\nOur team of engineers, geologists, landman and other professionals have a strong experience base. We are committed to capturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking, and strategic relationships. This translates to being able to execute on leasing, drilling and acquisitions in the most efficient and effective manner.\r\n\r\n<strong>Experienced Vertical and Horizontal Driller</strong>\r\n\r\nWe have a dedicated team of drilling and completion engineers as well as development geologists that have drilled and completed over 500 operated wells in the last 16 years with nearly 300 of those in the modern horizontal environment.\r\n\r\n<strong>Active Producing Property Buyer</strong>\r\n\r\nWith over 30 years of demonstrated acquisition experience to evaluate and pay for producing and undeveloped reserves, FourPoint has closed dozens of acquisition transactions ranging in size from less than $1 million to $1 Billion.\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsible Operator</strong>\r\n\r\nWe are a prudent, responsible, low cost operator. We have a disciplined approach to efficiency and cost reduction. Our technical team is highly experienced in drilling and completions in both horizontal and vertical wells. We are committed to the safe and environmentally responsible development of our energy resources and invest time and resources to improve the communities in which we live and work.\r\n\r\n<strong>Relationship Driven</strong>\r\n\r\nOur acquisition strategy incorporates a win-win philosophy to deal making. We strive to build long-term relationships and partnerships that lead to additional transactions down the road.\r\n\r\n<strong>Farmouts and Joint-Ventures</strong>\r\n\r\nWe encourage owners to provide us the opportunity to accelerate the development of their acreage via farmout or joint-venture agreements.\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact for Leasing</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Scott Haselwood</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Senior Land Advisor, Manager of Leasing\r\n(303) 785-1547 (direct)\r\n(303) 290-9997 (fax)\r\n(303) 720-877-1564 (cell)\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact for Asset Sales</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Brad Marvin</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Vice President, Business Development\r\n(303) 785-1554 (direct)\r\n(303) 290-9997 (fax)\r\n(303) 974-0275 (cell)\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Main areas of focus for leasing and asset acquisitions</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Active Plays: </span></h4>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Western Anadarko Basin:</strong> Texas Panhandle &amp; Western Oklahoma</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Permian Basin:</strong> Delaware and Midland Basins</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Areas of Focus:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>New Mexico: Lea, Eddy</li>\r\n 	<li>Texas: Loving, Culberson, Winkler, Ward, Reeves, Martin, Howard, Glasscock, Midland, Upton, Reagan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Operating Counties:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Texas: Hansford, Hemphill, Hutchinson, Lipscomb, Ochiltree, Roberts and Wheeler</li>\r\n 	<li>Oklahoma: Beckham, Blaine, Caddo, Canadian, Cleveland, Comanche, Custer, Dewey, Ellis, Garvin, Grady, McClain, Roger Mills, Washita and Woodward</li>\r\n</ul>','Business Opportunities','','inherit','closed','closed','','71-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 16:53:12','2016-05-24 16:53:12','',71,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/71-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(863,2,'2016-05-24 17:02:43','2016-05-24 17:02:43','<h3>Why lease or sell to FourPoint Energy?</h3>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></h4>\r\n<strong>Aggressive Offers</strong>\r\n\r\nWe pay at or above market based terms and are experienced to move quickly on simple or complex trades.\r\n\r\n<strong>Defined Areas of Focus</strong>\r\n\r\nOur leasing is focused on areas where FourPoint actively drills and operates.\r\n\r\n<strong>Active Developer</strong>\r\n\r\nWe are not an asset warehouse. Our business strategy employs an acquisition development model that accelerates the pace of value creation.\r\n\r\n<strong>Financial Strength</strong>\r\n\r\nAs a privately funded company, we have a strong balance sheet with over $2.5 billion of committed capital and backing from some of the largest funds in private equity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Highly Experienced Team</strong>\r\n\r\nOur team of engineers, geologists, landman and other professionals have a strong experience base. We are committed to capturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking, and strategic relationships. This translates to being able to execute on leasing, drilling and acquisitions in the most efficient and effective manner.\r\n\r\n<strong>Experienced Vertical and Horizontal Driller</strong>\r\n\r\nWe have a dedicated team of drilling and completion engineers as well as development geologists that have drilled and completed over 500 operated wells in the last 16 years with nearly 300 of those in the modern horizontal environment.\r\n\r\n<strong>Active Producing Property Buyer</strong>\r\n\r\nWith over 30 years of demonstrated acquisition experience to evaluate and pay for producing and undeveloped reserves, FourPoint has closed dozens of acquisition transactions ranging in size from less than $1 million to $1 Billion.\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsible Operator</strong>\r\n\r\nWe are a prudent, responsible, low cost operator. We have a disciplined approach to efficiency and cost reduction. Our technical team is highly experienced in drilling and completions in both horizontal and vertical wells. We are committed to the safe and environmentally responsible development of our energy resources and invest time and resources to improve the communities in which we live and work.\r\n\r\n<strong>Relationship Driven</strong>\r\n\r\nOur acquisition strategy incorporates a win-win philosophy to deal making. We strive to build long-term relationships and partnerships that lead to additional transactions down the road.\r\n\r\n<strong>Farmouts and Joint-Ventures</strong>\r\n\r\nWe encourage owners to provide us the opportunity to accelerate the development of their acreage via farmout or joint-venture agreements.\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact for Leasing</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Scott Haselwood</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Senior Land Advisor, Manager of Leasing\r\n(303) 785-1547 (direct)\r\n(303) 290-9997 (fax)\r\n(303) 720-877-1564 (cell)\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact for Asset Sales</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Brad Marvin</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Vice President, Business Development\r\n(303) 785-1554 (direct)\r\n(303) 290-9997 (fax)\r\n(303) 974-0275 (cell)\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Main areas of focus for leasing and asset acquisitions</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Active Plays: </span></h4>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Western Anadarko Basin:</strong> Texas Panhandle &amp; Western Oklahoma</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Permian Basin:</strong> Delaware and Midland Basins</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Areas of Focus:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>New Mexico:</strong> Lea, Eddy</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Texas:</strong> Loving, Culberson, Winkler, Ward, Reeves, Martin, Howard, Glasscock, Midland, Upton, Reagan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Operating Counties:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Texas:</strong> Hansford, Hemphill, Hutchinson, Lipscomb, Ochiltree, Roberts and Wheeler</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Oklahoma:</strong> Beckham, Blaine, Caddo, Canadian, Cleveland, Comanche, Custer, Dewey, Ellis, Garvin, Grady, McClain, Roger Mills, Washita and Woodward</li>\r\n</ul>','Business Opportunities','','inherit','closed','closed','','71-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 17:02:43','2016-05-24 17:02:43','',71,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/71-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(864,3,'2016-05-24 17:11:35','2016-05-24 17:11:35','<h3>Focus</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Core areas with concentrated assets</li>\r\n 	<li>Opportunities for organic growth and acquisition growth</li>\r\n 	<li>Long life gas reserves in active plays and basins</li>\r\n 	<li>High margin, repeatable plays driven by good geology, engineering, high margins, and strong upside</li>\r\n 	<li>Growth in production, cash flow, and reserves</li>\r\n 	<li>Focus Areas: Western Anadarko and Permian Basins</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>People and Culture</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Practicing and living out company values and behaviors (hyperlink to values)</li>\r\n 	<li>A results driven culture of opportunistic, performance-driven, and goal-oriented employees/partners</li>\r\n 	<li>Experts in core areas by fine tuning the geologic/engineering model</li>\r\n 	<li>Creative and adaptive to an always changing environment</li>\r\n 	<li>Deliberate and selective - Building a team of “A” players</li>\r\n 	<li>Develop a strong plan’ execute on the plan; stay focused and do it again and again</li>\r\n 	<li>Dedicated to value creation with a sense of urgency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Organic Oriented Growth</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Become the lessee of choice in each core area by doing what we said we’d do – be good stewards of the land and create value for our shareholders, landowners, royalty owners and communities in which we work</li>\r\n 	<li>Build concentrated areas of leasehold to pursue a multi-rig drilling program to maximize efficiency and lessen delays in production and reserve growth</li>\r\n 	<li>Emphasize geographic areas with quality production and reserve targets</li>\r\n 	<li>Strive for win-win negotiations with landowners and surface owners to maximize the benefit to each party while mitigating the impact of our operations on the environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Acquire &amp; Exploit Oriented Growth</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Aggressively pursue the purchase of producing properties in our core areas when we can capture additional upside opportunities, acquire additional leasehold, lower costs, and increase production and cash flow</li>\r\n 	<li>Develop and build relationships, deliver results, make more deals</li>\r\n 	<li>Pursue unsolicited and pre-emptive offers on assets that we can be an aggressive buyer</li>\r\n 	<li>Evaluate and pursue only those competitive transactions where we have a distinctive competence which will make us the most competitive buyer</li>\r\n 	<li>Be efficient and effective at multiple evaluations</li>\r\n 	<li>Stay in the market at all times as a buyer and seller</li>\r\n 	<li>Achieve critical mass in each core area through consistent growth in reserves, production, and cash flow</li>\r\n 	<li>Aggressively exploit upside opportunities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Financial Flexibility</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Seek strong, flexible, patient and market-savvy equity partners</li>\r\n 	<li>Preserve enough capital to weather dramatic changes in commodity prices</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintain a strong relationship with commercial banks to utilize debt as a meaningful, but fiscally prudent, part of the capital structure</li>\r\n 	<li>Seek hedging opportunities that help to secure expenditures on drilling and underpin acquisition economics</li>\r\n</ul>','Business Strategy','','inherit','closed','closed','','78-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 17:11:35','2016-05-24 17:11:35','',78,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/78-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(865,2,'2016-05-24 17:21:50','2016-05-24 17:21:50','FourPoint values the power of relationships, specifically those with our surface and mineral interest owners. To better serve our owners, FourPoint offers easy ways for owners to access copies of revenue checks and joint interest billings electronically. Additionally, we have provided easy instructions on how to read both your revenue check stub and your joint interest billing statements. We have also provided information on ownership changes and answers to frequently asked questions.\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<h3>Owner relation inquiries:</h3>\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a>\r\n\r\n(303) 785-1581\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3>Division Order Inquiries:</h3>\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:divisionorders@fourpointnergy.com\">divisionorders@fourpointnergy.com</a>\r\n\r\n</div>','Owner Information','','inherit','closed','closed','','187-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 17:21:50','2016-05-24 17:21:50','',187,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/187-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(866,2,'2016-05-24 17:28:49','2016-05-24 17:28:49','This list provides the documentation FourPoint Energy will need in order to complete the change to your ownership account. All change requests must be submitted in writing.\r\n\r\nShould you have any additional questions regarding the documentation required to complete a change to your account, please feel free to contact us at (303) 785-1581 or <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Address Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Submit request in writing with your signature</li>\r\n 	<li>New W-9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Appointment of Attorney-In-Fact</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Copy of Power of Attorney</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Bankruptcy - Chapter 7</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Recorded conveyance (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Order naming trustee of bankruptcy estate</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Bankruptcy - Chapter 11</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Plan of reorganization</li>\r\n 	<li>Order confirming the plan of reorganization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Changes in Trustee</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Instrument by which the Successor Trustee was appointed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Company Name Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Certificate of Name Change including Tax I.D.</li>\r\n 	<li>New W-9 Company Name</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Change Due to Merger</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Certificate of Merger including Tax I.D.</li>\r\n 	<li>New W-9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner with a will that has not been probated</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Affidavit of Heirship (Signed by a person who is not an heir)</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner with a will with probate proceedings conducted in the state where the property is located</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Order admitting will to probate</li>\r\n 	<li>Letters testamentary</li>\r\n 	<li>Last will and testament</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner with a will with probate proceedings conducted outside the state where the property is located</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Order admitting will to probate</li>\r\n 	<li>Letters testamentary</li>\r\n 	<li>Last will and testament</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession</li>\r\n 	<li>Documentation of ancillary probate proceedings opened in all affected states or affidavit of heirship (signed by person who is not an heir)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner without a will</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Letters of administration</li>\r\n 	<li>Affidavit of Heirship (Signed by a person who is not an heir)</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Enroll or change in revenue direct deposit</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Submit new direct deposit form with voided check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Joint Tenancy with Death of One Tenant</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate of deceased tenant Life Estate - Death</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Life tenant\'s Death Certificate</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Names and addresses of remaindermen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Name Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Marriage Certificate or Divorce Decree reinstating maiden name or other legal document of name change</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Ownership Change Due to Divorce</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Complete Divorce Decree including Settlement Agreement and recorded conveyances (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Sale of Interest</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Complete copy of conveyance document filed of record in the county which the property is located</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Trust or Partnership Creation or Dissolution</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Trust or Partnership Agreement and recorded conveyance(s) (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','Change of Ownership','','inherit','closed','closed','','197-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 17:28:49','2016-05-24 17:28:49','',197,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/197-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(867,2,'2016-05-24 17:30:31','2016-05-24 17:30:31','This list provides the documentation FourPoint Energy will need in order to complete the change to your ownership account. All change requests must be submitted in writing.\r\n\r\nShould you have any additional questions regarding the documentation required to complete a change to your account, please feel free to contact us at (303) 785-1581 or <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Address Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Submit request in writing with your signature</li>\r\n 	<li>New W-9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Appointment of Attorney-In-Fact</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Copy of Power of Attorney</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Bankruptcy - Chapter 7</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Recorded conveyance (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Order naming trustee of bankruptcy estate</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Bankruptcy - Chapter 11</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Plan of reorganization</li>\r\n 	<li>Order confirming the plan of reorganization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Changes in Trustee</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Instrument by which the Successor Trustee was appointed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Company Name Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Certificate of Name Change including Tax I.D.</li>\r\n 	<li>New W-9 Company Name</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Change Due to Merger</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Certificate of Merger including Tax I.D.</li>\r\n 	<li>New W-9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner with a will that has not been probated</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Affidavit of Heirship (Signed by a person who is not an heir)</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner with a will with probate proceedings conducted in the state where the property is located</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Order admitting will to probate</li>\r\n 	<li>Letters testamentary</li>\r\n 	<li>Last will and testament</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner with a will with probate proceedings conducted outside the state where the property is located</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Order admitting will to probate</li>\r\n 	<li>Letters testamentary</li>\r\n 	<li>Last will and testament</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession</li>\r\n 	<li>Documentation of ancillary probate proceedings opened in all affected states or affidavit of heirship (signed by person who is not an heir)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Death of owner without a will</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Letters of administration</li>\r\n 	<li>Affidavit of Heirship (Signed by a person who is not an heir)</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence debts and taxes have been paid</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Enroll or change in revenue direct deposit</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Submit new direct deposit form with voided check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Joint Tenancy with Death of One Tenant</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Death Certificate of deceased tenant Life Estate - Death</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Life tenant\'s Death Certificate</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Names and addresses of remaindermen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Name Change</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Marriage Certificate or Divorce Decree reinstating maiden name or other legal document of name change</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Ownership Change Due to Divorce</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Complete Divorce Decree including Settlement Agreement and recorded conveyances (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Sale of Interest</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Complete copy of conveyance document filed of record in the county which the property is located</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Trust or Partnership Creation or Dissolution</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Trust or Partnership Agreement and recorded conveyance(s) (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Legal Advice</em></strong>\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy is unable to provide legal advice. Please contact an attorney for any questions regarding legal advice.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>IRS Form W-9</em></strong>\r\n\r\nFederal law requires all owners to provide their social security number or tax identification number via an IRS Form W-9 (hyperlink to download form). Should you fail to provide this information, you may become subject to non-refundable backup withholding.','Change of Ownership','','inherit','closed','closed','','197-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 17:30:31','2016-05-24 17:30:31','',197,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/197-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(868,2,'2016-05-24 17:34:45','2016-05-24 17:34:45','<h2>How do I contact FourPoint Energy?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Visit our <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/contact/\">\"Contact Us\"</a> page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How do I make changes to my account?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Visit our <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/interest-owners/change-of-ownership/\">“Change of Ownership”</a> section</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Can I setup direct deposit of revenue checks?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Download our direct deposit form. Please print the form, complete it in its entirety and return by mail along with a voided check to: 100 Saint Paul Street, Suite 400, Denver, CO 80206 or email us at: ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>I returned my direct deposit form. Why did I receive another check in the mail?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please allow 60 days for us to process your direct deposit request. If you mailed your form more than 60 days ago, please contact us at (303) 785-1581 or <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Why have I not received a revenue check?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Revenue checks are mailed monthly by the last day of the second month following the month of production. Revenue checks are mailed to all owners with a balance due to them of over $100.00. If the balance on your account is not over $100.00, a revenue check may not be issued to you each month. Once a year, typically in the spring, revenue checks will be mailed to all owners with a balance due to them of over $10.00.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Can I receive my revenue checks even if the account balance is under $100.00?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please submit a request in writing with the dollar amount you would like to have revenue checks mailed to you, to <a href=\"mailto:ownerinq@cordilleraep.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>When can I expect to receive my 1099?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Your 1099 will be mailed to you no later than January 31st. Please allow 10 business days after January 31st before contacting us regarding not receiving your 1099.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What should I do if my check is lost or stolen?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please allow 10 business days after checks are mailed to receive your check. If after 10 business days you have still not received your revenue check please contact us at (303) 785-1581 or <a href=\"mailto:ownerinq@cordilleraep.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a>. If your check is stolen please contact us at (303) 785-1581 or <a href=\"mailto:ownerinq@cordilleraep.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How do I get a copy of my revenue check or joint interest billing?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>All revenue check detail is available at <a href=\"http://www.energylink.com/\">www.energylink.com</a>. Please contact us at (303) 785-1581 or <a href=\"mailto:ownerinq@cordilleraep.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a> to receive your user ID and password for EnergyLink.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Why did you send me an IRS Form W-9?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The IRS requires that we confirm your Tax ID number every year and keep the W-9 on file. Please complete the form using the name provided on your revenue check, and your Social Security number or Tax ID number.</li>\r\n</ul>','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','514-revision-v1','','','2016-05-24 17:34:45','2016-05-24 17:34:45','',514,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/24/514-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
