s=\"s1\"><b>Main areas of focus for leasing and asset acquisitions:</b></span></h3>\r\n<h2>Active Plays:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Western Anadarko Basin\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n\r\nThe Western Anadarko Basin is located in western Oklahoma and the eastern panhandle of Texas.  This prolific hydrocarbon province contains dense vertical well control and is characterized over twenty gas and oil productive horizons across an area of that covers over 5 million acres.\r\n\r\n</div></li>\r\n 	<li>Delaware Basin</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Delaware Basin, spanning portions of both West Texas and SE New Mexico, is the western of the two sub-basins found within the Greater Permian Basin.  Prolific production of both oil and gas from thick accumulations of hydrocarbon saturated Permian age sediments provide multiple stacked target opportunities. The productive fairway of intervals such as the Delaware Group, Avalon, Bone Spring, and Wolfcamp cover an area of more than 5 million acres.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Midland Basin\r\nThe Midland Basin of West Texas is the eastern of the two sub-basins found within the Greater Permian Basin. This dominantly oil producing region is characterized by thick accumulations of Permian age sediments, with a productive fairway spanning close to 6 million acres. Thousands of feet of hydrocarbon saturated column including intervals such as the Spraberry, Wolfcamp, and Cline provide multiple stacked target opportunities across this broad region.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2> Operating Counties:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Texas:</strong> Hansford, Hemphill, Hutchinson, Lipscomb, Ochiltree, Roberts and Wheeler</li>\r\n 	<li><strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Oklahoma:</strong> Beckham, Blaine, Caddo, Canadian, Cleveland, Comanche, Custer, Dewey, Ellis, Garvin, Grady, McClain, Roger Mills, Washita and Woodward</li>\r\n</ul>','Business Opportunities','','inherit','closed','closed','